HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1549
By Pearson
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend St. Jude Children's
Research Hospital in Memphis for its
groundbreaking leadership in HIV/AIDS
treatment, research, prevention, and
compassionate care for children, families, and
communities.
WHEREAS, St. Jude Children's Research Hospital has stood for decades as a global
leader in advancing care for catastrophic diseases affecting children, including pioneering
efforts in the treatment and prevention of human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) and acquired
immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS); and
WHEREAS, in the earliest days of the HIV/AIDS epidemic in the 1980s, St. Jude made
the moral and scientific commitment to confront this disease in children, establishing one of the
nation's leading pediatric HIV research and care programs and helping transform HIV from a
fatal diagnosis into a manageable chronic condition; and
WHEREAS, St. Jude is home to a nationally recognized Pediatric AIDS Clinical Trials
Unit, designated a Center of Excellence, where children and youth gain access to cutting-edge
therapies and clinical trials and where many of the medications now approved for pediatric HIV
treatment were studied and advanced; and
WHEREAS, through its multidisciplinary HIV program, St. Jude provides comprehensive,
lifelong care—combining antiretroviral therapy, mental health services, social support, and
transitional care—ensuring that young people living with HIV can lead long, healthy, and
dignified lives; and
WHEREAS, the hospital's Perinatal HIV Program has played a critical role in
dramatically reducing mother-to-child transmission of HIV, helping achieve transmission rates of
HJR1549
018107
- 1 -

less than one percent when proper medical care is provided, thereby protecting future
generations; and
WHEREAS, St. Jude researchers and clinicians have contributed to groundbreaking
advances in HIV science, including studies that shaped prevention strategies, improved drug
therapies, and expanded access to long-acting and injectable treatments that reduce barriers to
adherence; and
WHEREAS, through its leadership in national and international research networks,
including NIH-supported trials and prevention initiatives, St. Jude continues to drive innovation
in HIV treatment and prevention, ensuring that the most vulnerable populations are not left
behind; and
WHEREAS, recognizing that health outcomes are shaped by more than medicine alone,
St. Jude has led community-centered initiatives such as Connect 2 Protect and Operation Zero,
working to eliminate new HIV infections in Memphis by 2030 through education, outreach, and
collaboration; and
WHEREAS, in a region disproportionately impacted by HIV, particularly among young
people, St. Jude has served as a one-stop center for testing, treatment, prevention, and
education, reducing stigma and expanding access to lifesaving care; and
WHEREAS, the work of St. Jude embodies a commitment not only to scientific
excellence but to justice, dignity, and the belief that every child, regardless of circumstance,
deserves the opportunity to live a full and healthy life; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend St. Jude Children's Research Hospital for its
extraordinary leadership in the fight against HIV/AIDS and its enduring commitment to the
health and future of children and families in Tennessee and around the world.
- 2 - 018107

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
